{"parse":{"title":"The Last Gospel (novel)","pageid":33172309,"revid":796288774,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">The Last Gospel <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Last+Gospel&amp;rft.author=David+Gibbins&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.pub=Headline+%28UK%29%2C+Bantam+Dell+%28US%29&amp;rft.pages=418+%28hardback%29&amp;rft.series=Jack+Howard+series\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;display:none\"><div>Cover of first UK edition 2008</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\nDavid Gibbins</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Cover&#160;artist</th><td>\nStephen Mulcahey</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUK</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Series</th><td>\nJack Howard series</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\narchaeological thriller</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\nHeadline (UK), Bantam Dell (US)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n2008</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nhardback, paperback and ebook</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n418 (hardback)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-7553-3514-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-7553-3514-5\">978-0-7553-3514-5</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Preceded&#160;by</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/wiki/Crusader_Gold_(novel)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crusader Gold (novel)\">Crusader Gold</a></i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Followed&#160;by</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Tiger_Warrior_(novel)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Tiger Warrior (novel)\">The Tiger Warrior</a></i></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Last Gospel</b></i> (titled <i><b>The Lost Tomb</b></i> in the US) is an archaeological adventure novel by <a href=\"/wiki/David_Gibbins\" title=\"David Gibbins\">David Gibbins</a>. First published in 2008, it is the third book in Gibbins' Jack Howard series. It has been published in more than 20 languages and was a London Sunday Times top-ten bestseller <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/public/sitesearch.do?querystring=David+Gibbins&amp;p=tto&amp;pf=all&amp;bl=on\">[1]</a> and a New York Times top-ten bestseller <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9400E6DD103AF93AA35752C1A96E9C8B63&amp;scp=14&amp;sq=David%20Gibbins&amp;st=cse\">[2]</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Other_language_editions\">Other language editions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Last_Gospel_(novel)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Other language editions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Among its international editions <i><b>The Last Gospel</b></i> is titled <i><b>Le Dernier Evangile</b></i> in France and <i><b>Il Vangelo proibito</b></i> in Italy <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://blog.newtoncompton.com/il-vangelo-proibito/\">[3]</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Plot_summary\">Plot summary</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Last_Gospel_(novel)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Plot summary\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>1st century CE: the lame <a href=\"/wiki/Claudius\" title=\"Claudius\">Claudius</a>, not yet Emperor of Rome, travels in the year 23 to Galilee where he meets a charismatic young carpenter, Joshua of Nazareth, and is inspired by his philosophy of heaven on earth. Claudius records the carpenter\u2019s words on a scroll that he takes back to Rome. Later, after the Nazarene is crucified, Claudius becomes emperor. He fakes his own death and disappears from imperial Rome to contrive an ingenuous plan to hide this secret gospel of Christ from those who would destroy it. 21st century: archaeologist Jack Howard and his team of researchers first learn of this last gospel when excavating Claudius\u2019s secret library near Pompeii. Following the trail of clues Claudius has laid out, their quest takes them from Italy to London, California, and finally Jerusalem. All the while the mafia and elite Vatican henchmen are hot on their heels, willing to stop at nothing to prevent Christ\u2019s true message from being discovered. Eventually they find the Gospel of Jesus. In the epilogue the whole scene of Claudius meeting Jesus is shown. The words of the Gospel are: \" The Kingdom of heaven is on Earth. No one shall stand in the way of the word of God. There shall be no Priests. And there shall be no Temples.\"\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Last_Gospel_(novel)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.davidgibbins.com\">David Gibbins' website</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1324\nCached time: 20180908230439\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.100 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.160 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 823/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include